General case of sub-Gaussian random variables
The proof of Hoeffding's inequality can be generalized to any sub-Gaussian distribution. Recall that a random variable X is called sub-Gaussian, if 

  
    
      
        
          P
        
        (
        
          |
        
        X
        
          |
        
        ≥
        t
